                    <span>This book is a marvelous, life-enriching reading experience, and a sports classic that should stand for years to come. I read a childhood biography of Gehrig by Van Riper at the age of 8 or 9 that left me hooked on reading in general and Gehrig in particular, and this is the bio he has deserved and I have longed for, for years. Highest recommendation!</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">The Pride of Baseball</div>
                    <div>
